{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime of $25,000 and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, sentencing guidelines for first-time, relatively low-amount white-collar offenses generally favor shorter periods of incarceration or alternative sentencing to allow for full restitution. The outburst from the spectator is disregarded as it has no bearing on the legal merits or the pre-sentencing report. A period of confinement of 6 months is sufficient to address the criminality while allowing the defendant to maintain employment to finish paying back the employer.",
  "verdict": 6
}
